ZCZC OE31
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 092300 UTC
DURING TUESDAY EVENING AND WEDNESDAY THE AZORES HIGH PRESSURE AREA WILL
EXTEND A RIDGE ACROSS THE WERN AND NERN ISLES CONNECTING TO ANOTHER HIGH
PRESSURE CENTRE OVER SCANDINAVIA. LOW PRESSURE AREAS WILL LIE ACROSS SPAIN
AND FRANCE 1010 WITH A TROUGH OF LOW PRESSURE ACROSS BRITAIN. ATLANTIC LOW
PRESSURE AREA 999 WILL BECOME CENTRED W OF ICELAND. A SIMILAR PRESSURE PATTERN
WILL PERSIST THROUGH THURSDAY WITH LOW PRESSURE 1010 OVER FRANCE AND SERN
BRITAIN WITH HIGH PRESSURE NEAR THE AZORES AND MID-ATLANTIC RUNNING ACROSS
NERN SCOTLAND TOWARDS THE BALTIC. LOW PRESSURE 985 WILL BE LOCATED N OF ICELAND.
THERE IS LOWER CONFIDENCE IN DETAIL FOR FRIDAY WITH THE POSSIBILITY OF AN
ATLANTIC RIDGE EXTENDING ACROSS THE BRITISH ISLES. WINDS MAY BE OCNL STRG
THROUGH THE PERIOD ESPECIALLY S AND N BUT LOW CONFIDENCE IN DETAIL ESPECIALLY
TOWARDS FRIDAY. STRGER GUSTS ARE POSS NEAR SQUALLY THUNDERY SHWRS IN S.
OCCASIONAL GALES ARE POSS IN SE ICELAND ON THURSDAY AND FRIDAY
